WEBVTT

00:31.323 --> 00:34.617
JONATHAN: America has produced
only three classic writers,

00:34.702 --> 00:38.121
Mark Twain, J.D. Salinger, and me.

00:40.040 --> 00:42.083
I'm Jonathan Flynn.

00:42.167 --> 00:44.627
Everything I write is a masterpiece.

00:45.379 --> 00:48.172
And soon, very soon,

00:49.007 --> 00:50.883
I shall be known.

00:56.598 --> 00:59.892
At this point of the story,
let's call it the present,

00:59.977 --> 01:03.730
I am an upstanding citizen
of these United States.

01:03.814 --> 01:05.773
I have a job,

01:05.983 --> 01:09.694
a roof over my head. I have sustenance.

01:12.197 --> 01:14.782
Perhaps I'll let you read
my masterpiece someday.

01:15.033 --> 01:18.536
The Button Man, also known as The
Confessions of Christopher Cobb.

01:18.620 --> 01:20.121
It's classic.

01:25.210 --> 01:26.627
NICK: This isn't his story.

01:26.712 --> 01:30.089
Well, it is, but he is not telling it,

01:30.924 --> 01:32.133
I am.

01:34.636 --> 01:38.681
I'm Nick Flynn, his son, and I am
sort of trying to be a writer.

01:42.019 --> 01:43.936
I mean, not at this very moment.

01:44.021 --> 01:45.438
At this moment I'm trying to...

01:45.522 --> 01:46.814
Wake up.

01:47.357 --> 01:48.441
(CLEARS THROAT)

01:49.193 --> 01:51.068
Hey, wake up.

01:58.577 --> 02:02.663
All my life, my father has been
manifest as an absence.

02:02.748 --> 02:05.875
A non-presence. A name without a body.

02:05.959 --> 02:07.126
What if he doesn't show up?

02:07.211 --> 02:08.669
He's gonna show up.

02:08.753 --> 02:10.045
How do you know?

02:10.130 --> 02:12.673
Because if he doesn't show up this time,

02:12.758 --> 02:14.634
I'm going to kill him.

02:15.052 --> 02:16.928
How will you find him to kill him?

02:18.430 --> 02:20.223
I have ways.

02:22.810 --> 02:25.353
Can we get ice cream if
he doesn't show up?

02:26.605 --> 02:28.523
Here is the bus. Here he is.

02:33.111 --> 02:34.612
JODY: No, that is not him.

02:35.405 --> 02:36.948
He must be in the back.

03:02.182 --> 03:03.266
(SNIFFLES)

03:03.934 --> 03:05.268
What kind of ice cream do you want to get?

03:05.394 --> 03:06.727
Chocolate.

03:07.604 --> 03:10.398
NICK: Some part of me knew
he would show up someday.

03:10.482 --> 03:13.901
If I stayed in one place long
enough, he would find me,

03:13.986 --> 03:17.154
like you are taught to
do when you are lost.

03:17.239 --> 03:18.906
But what do you do if both of you are lost

03:18.991 --> 03:21.576
and you both end up in the
same place, waiting?

03:36.300 --> 03:37.550
Hey, sweetie.

03:37.634 --> 03:38.926
Hey.

03:42.347 --> 03:43.681
I'm exhausted.

03:43.765 --> 03:44.765
How was your flight?

03:44.850 --> 03:46.225
Non-stop turbulence.

03:47.352 --> 03:49.103
Nick, what is the ashtray
doing by the bed?

03:50.731 --> 03:51.939
Sorry.

03:54.151 --> 03:55.151
Lipstick?

03:58.363 --> 04:00.406
You are a fucking asshole.

04:02.242 --> 04:04.911
Look, you are the one who said you
didn't see a future for us.

04:04.995 --> 04:07.163
I wonder why? This is yours!

04:08.749 --> 04:09.916
This is yours.

04:10.000 --> 04:11.751
And this is yours! All right.

04:11.835 --> 04:13.502
And this is yours. All right.

04:13.587 --> 04:15.171
My book. And Yates.

04:15.589 --> 04:17.589
Oh, more Yates. All right.

04:17.673 --> 04:19.341
Wow! You are so well-read.

04:19.426 --> 04:21.344
All right. All right!

04:35.692 --> 04:36.901
I'll pay for the mirror.

04:38.487 --> 04:39.862
As soon as I get a job.

04:43.492 --> 04:44.575
Sorry.

04:46.995 --> 04:49.830
For what, your complete inadequacy
as a human being?

04:52.668 --> 04:53.751
Yes.

04:54.461 --> 04:55.586
(SCOFFS)

04:57.589 --> 04:59.548
Well, you warned me.

05:01.093 --> 05:02.218
JONATHAN: Don't worry, you're back.

05:02.511 --> 05:03.511
Hello.

05:03.595 --> 05:06.806
Back in the hands of a master storyteller.

05:07.182 --> 05:08.349
(WOMAN SPEAKING IN SPANISH)

05:09.893 --> 05:11.477
Yeah, yeah, go fuck yourself.

05:12.980 --> 05:14.897
I like kids and small animals.

05:15.732 --> 05:17.900
What I don't like is queers and blacks

05:18.026 --> 05:21.320
who try and fuck you up the
ass all day and all night.

05:21.405 --> 05:22.405
But more on that later.

05:24.866 --> 05:27.868
What I am, always have been, is an artist.

05:29.788 --> 05:31.247
(ROCK MUSIC BLARING)

05:38.005 --> 05:40.006
Shut the fuck up.

05:42.509 --> 05:44.218
Shut up. Shut up.

05:44.803 --> 05:46.012
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

06:02.237 --> 06:03.237
(MUSIC STOPS)

06:03.989 --> 06:05.197
(MUSIC BLARING)

06:05.282 --> 06:10.119
Shut the fuck up! Shut up!

06:10.787 --> 06:12.538
Shut up!

06:13.290 --> 06:14.999
NICK: A friend of a friend
knew a couple of guys

06:15.083 --> 06:16.709
who were renting an entire building,

06:16.793 --> 06:19.628
a former strip joint called "Good Times."

06:19.713 --> 06:23.215
Unfortunately, the good times
were not had by all,

06:23.300 --> 06:24.967
like that Harvard student who was found

06:25.052 --> 06:27.219
stabbed to death in the doorway
three years before.

06:27.304 --> 06:28.304
(SIREN WAILING)

06:36.646 --> 06:37.688
(DOORBELL BUZZES)

06:37.898 --> 06:38.981
IVAN: I don't know what to tell you.

06:39.066 --> 06:40.775
That's something you got
to figure out, man.

06:40.859 --> 06:42.943
So, what appeals to you about living here?

06:43.820 --> 06:45.821
Low rent. IVAN: Yeah, hold on one second.

06:46.198 --> 06:47.531
Do you have a job?

06:47.741 --> 06:49.992
Uh, no. I have some money saved up.

06:50.077 --> 06:51.744
I was working as an electrician,

06:51.828 --> 06:53.704
but now I'm looking for
a new line of work.

06:53.789 --> 06:54.872
IVAN: An electrician?

06:54.998 --> 06:56.916
Can you wire this place up
to look like a spaceship?

06:57.000 --> 06:58.334
(WHISPERS) Ivan. Yes.

06:59.878 --> 07:02.338
And what field of employment
are you interested in?

07:03.131 --> 07:04.965
Something different, something
more meaningful.

07:05.050 --> 07:06.467
"More meaningful," what does that mean?

07:09.513 --> 07:10.763
I don't know.

07:10.847 --> 07:12.389
Are those, like, the names of strippers?

07:12.474 --> 07:15.684
Yeah. The landlord's Mafia, so he just
left all this shit the way it was

07:15.769 --> 07:17.144
when the FBI shut him down.

07:17.229 --> 07:18.521
RICHARD: Any family?

07:18.605 --> 07:19.897
Stop interrogating the guy.

07:19.981 --> 07:22.024
I'm sorry, Ivan, but my last roommate had

07:22.109 --> 07:24.693
