sleeping in the living room.

07:24.778 --> 07:28.197
No, my mom's dead, and my dad, I haven't
heard from in 18 years, so...

07:28.824 --> 07:29.865
Perfect. Done.

07:31.201 --> 07:32.409
So, are you guys like...

07:32.494 --> 07:34.036
No. No. Okay.

07:34.871 --> 07:38.958
So, Denise, didn't you say they were
hiring people at your work?

07:39.042 --> 07:40.126
They usually are.

07:40.210 --> 07:42.503
Good. 'Cause I think Nick here
is looking for a job.

07:42.587 --> 07:44.380
Give him a break, man. Where do you work?

07:45.048 --> 07:46.465
Harbor Street Inn. You heard of it?

07:46.550 --> 07:48.217
No. It's a homeless shelter.

07:50.220 --> 07:53.639
That sounds intense. So are
you like a do-gooder?

07:53.723 --> 07:57.226
No, I'm a do-badder, but
I work at Harbor Street.

07:57.644 --> 07:59.520
What makes you a do-badder?

08:00.397 --> 08:01.480
I bet you would like to know.

08:01.731 --> 08:03.065
I would.

08:09.948 --> 08:12.825
JONATHAN: Upon occasion, rare
occasion, but still,

08:12.909 --> 08:16.579
I'll pick up a female fare and we
will strike up a conversation.

08:16.872 --> 08:18.289
WOMAN: Oh, Jonathan.

08:19.416 --> 08:21.083
Oh, Jonathan.

08:21.168 --> 08:22.251
(MOANING)

08:23.795 --> 08:24.837
Jonathan.

08:24.921 --> 08:25.963
Yeah.

08:26.047 --> 08:27.715
Let's be a little realistic here.

08:27.799 --> 08:29.258
All right.

08:31.178 --> 08:32.260
(PANTING)

08:35.307 --> 08:37.975
Still, we are having fun,
aren't we, Buttercup?

08:38.058 --> 08:39.434
Absolutely.

08:40.604 --> 08:41.770
Who is this?

08:41.855 --> 08:43.856
That is my wife and kid.

08:44.357 --> 08:46.275
Will you listen to this shit.
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

08:46.860 --> 08:48.527
You are married?

08:49.196 --> 08:51.280
Divorced, a long time ago.

08:52.991 --> 08:54.700
Well, I had better get you home.

08:55.035 --> 08:57.453
I left the meter running. That'll be $240.

08:57.662 --> 08:58.787
(LAUGHING)

09:00.457 --> 09:03.959
Quiet!

09:04.211 --> 09:06.795
I can't even think anymore!

09:13.094 --> 09:14.803
Excuse me.

09:17.265 --> 09:18.474
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

09:22.812 --> 09:24.146
Open up!

09:26.983 --> 09:28.651
Asshole.

09:31.488 --> 09:32.738
(CRASHING)

09:35.742 --> 09:37.284
(INDISTINCT SCREAMING)

09:38.495 --> 09:39.703
(CRASHING)

09:52.926 --> 09:54.426
NICK: Hey.

09:54.511 --> 09:55.511
Hey.

09:55.679 --> 09:57.680
I was hoping you'd be here.

09:58.348 --> 09:59.390
Why is that?

09:59.474 --> 10:00.474
Well, so I know somebody.

10:00.558 --> 10:03.102
We don't exactly know each other, do we?

10:03.561 --> 10:04.687
I guess not.

10:10.694 --> 10:13.195
I'm not interested in a relationship.

10:13.280 --> 10:14.280
What?

10:14.364 --> 10:15.864
I'm not interested in a relationship.

10:15.949 --> 10:17.658
Okay, I can cope.

10:17.742 --> 10:19.368
Okay.

10:23.915 --> 10:25.040
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

10:29.254 --> 10:30.296
Phone call.

10:31.381 --> 10:32.423
Who is it?

10:32.841 --> 10:33.882
Your father.

10:34.050 --> 10:35.050
Who?

10:35.135 --> 10:38.971
Your father, who you supposedly
hadn't seen in 18 years.

10:56.156 --> 10:57.323
This is Nick.

10:57.407 --> 10:58.365
JONATHAN: Is this Nicholas Flynn?

10:58.450 --> 10:59.491
Yes.

10:59.576 --> 11:02.619
Nicholas, this is your father,
Jonathan Flynn.

11:02.704 --> 11:03.787
It is?

11:03.872 --> 11:05.539
It is. I have a question for you.

11:05.623 --> 11:08.292
Do you have a truck? A pickup truck?

11:08.376 --> 11:10.085
Yeah, as a matter of fact, I do.

11:10.170 --> 11:11.628
I heard as much.

11:11.713 --> 11:12.796
From who?

11:12.881 --> 11:14.840
Your grandmother, she mentioned
it a few years ago.

11:14.924 --> 11:17.176
You do remember your grandmother,
don't you?

11:17.260 --> 11:18.385
I do. Good.

11:18.470 --> 11:20.929
Now I want you to get in your
truck and drive over here.

11:21.931 --> 11:23.182
I'm sorry, you say you are my father?

11:23.266 --> 11:24.308
That is correct.

11:24.392 --> 11:26.226
I was evicted and I need
you to get over here

11:26.311 --> 11:29.104
and help me move my stuff, Nicholas.

11:29.606 --> 11:30.856
How did you get this number?

11:30.940 --> 11:33.233
Information. Now listen to me carefully.

11:33.318 --> 11:35.319
I am sitting behind a door with a shotgun.

11:35.403 --> 11:37.488
I'm waiting for the knob to turn.

11:37.572 --> 11:39.656
Get over here right now.

11:40.283 --> 11:41.492
That is an appealing offer.

11:41.576 --> 11:43.035
You are damn right it is.

11:43.411 --> 11:45.788
It's all yours. You are
my sole heir, Nicholas.

11:45.872 --> 11:47.206
I want you to have everything.

11:47.290 --> 11:48.582
You have a pen or a pencil?

11:48.666 --> 11:50.667
Because I want you to write
this address down.

11:53.713 --> 11:55.547
What am I doing here?

11:55.632 --> 11:58.384
What are you doing here?
What are we doing here?

11:58.468 --> 12:00.135
Thanks for coming.

12:00.220 --> 12:04.098
Sure. Should we just wait here?
Or do you want us...

12:25.453 --> 12:26.412
JONATHAN: Who is it?

12:26.496 --> 12:28.539
It's Nick. Nicholas.

12:28.623 --> 12:31.041
Come on in, the door is open. Come in.

12:37.132 --> 12:38.382
I'll be with you in a minute.

12:41.052 --> 12:43.762
I appreciate you coming over, Nicholas.

12:43.847 --> 12:46.348
We're put on this Earth
to help other people.

12:46.558 --> 12:47.850
Yeah.

12:52.480 --> 12:55.315
JONATHAN: We were put on this Earth
to help other people, Nicholas.

12:55.400 --> 12:57.359
I regret our mutual loss.

12:57.444 --> 13:00.112
I am a born writer, so are you.

13:00.196 --> 13:04.908
Get this in your head at once. I am a
classic storyteller. A great writer.

13:04.993 --> 13:06.118
I think I want to be a writer.

13:06.202 --> 13:07.244
Yeah?

13:07.328 --> 13:08.787
Dad is a writer, right?

13:08.872 --> 13:09.955
Ha!

13:10.415 --> 13:11.957
What makes you think that?

13:12.041 --> 13:15.419
It says right here. It says, "Work
on my novel is going well.

13:15.712 --> 13:17.588
"I shall soon win the Nobel Prize

13:17.672 --> 13:19.465
"for both storytelling and poetry.

13:19.549 --> 13:21.175
"No fear."

13:22.051 --> 13:24.344
You know where that letter
was written from?

13:24.429 --> 13:25.554
Prison. Mmm-hmm.

13:25.722 --> 13:26.889
Why is he in prison again?

13:27.098 --> 13:29.683
Interstate transportation
of stolen securities.

13:29.767 --> 13:30.809
What is that?

13:30.894 --> 13:32.603
He cashed forged checks.

13:32.979 --> 13:36.857
He stole thousands and
thousands of dollars.

13:37.317 --> 13:38.484
Do you know how much of that we have seen?

13:38.693 --> 13:39.818
Zero. Zilch.

13:39.903 --> 13:41.320
Zippo. Nothing.

13:41.404 --> 13:43.071
Nada. Niente.

13:45.533 --> 13:47.075
Have you seen my baseball glove?

13:47.160 --> 13:49.703
If it were up your ass, you
would know where it was.

13:49.787 --> 13:50.871
(CHUCKLES)

13:54.834 --> 13:56.001
(DOOR OPENING)

13:56.419 --> 13:58.921
Well? Gonna come in?

14:08.014 --> 14:10.891
Pleasure to see you, Nicholas,
aside from the circumstances.

14:10.975 --> 14:12.267
NICK: What are the circumstances?

14:12.352 --> 14:13.685
The circumstances are

14:13.770 --> 14:16.855
that I had a disagreement with
my scum-sucking landlord.

14:17.607 --> 14:19.525
I don't know why.

14:19.609 --> 14:21.610
And so he decided to bring the
police into the discussion.

14:21.945 --> 14:23.070
So now I'm forced to move.

14:23.238 --> 14:24.488
Move where?

14:25.281 --> 14:27.950
I'm considering my options. I'm
a sought-after house guest.

14:28.034 --> 14:29.076
You know why?

14:29.953 --> 14:30.994
No.

14:31.079 --> 14:32.788
Because I'm an excellent raconteur.

14:34.165 --> 14:35.499
But until I find a new place,

14:35.583 --> 14:37.042
I have to put all my things in storage.

14:37.126 --> 14:38.627
Hey. So I'm not bringing
the gun in my truck.

14:39.295 --> 14:40.879
What? The shotgun.

14:40.964 --> 14:41.964
Shotgun?

14:42.048 --> 14:43.090
Uh, yeah. You said you had a shotgun.

14:43.174 --> 14:45.300
A shotgun? Who said that?
I abhor firearms.

14:45.552 --> 14:48.011
I mean, don't get me wrong,
I can defend myself.

14:48.137 --> 14:49.471
Let me just...

14:55.937 --> 14:57.354
You see this? Yes.

14:57.522 --> 14:59.022
Anyone messes with me when I'm driving

14:59.107 --> 15:00.566
or walking down the street, whatever.

15:00.775 --> 15:03.235
Bamo! Right in the head. It sends a
little message, let me tell you.

15:03.695 --> 15:04.945
I'd like to take that scumbag landlord,

15:05.029 --> 15:06.822
and I'd like to ram it right up his ass.

15:07.156 --> 15:09.866
This landlord, this merchant,
this fucking user...

15:09.951 --> 15:12.160
Hey, that is great. Would you
mind putting that away?

15:12.328 --> 15:13.662
I'd like to take this and...

15:13.746 --> 15:15.414
Please? ...ram it up his fucking ass,

15:15.498 --> 15:17.499
twist it around, pull it down,

15:17.625 --> 15:21.086
rip out his innards and
fucking pull them out.

15:21.170 --> 15:23.171
You get the fucking picture.

15:29.470 --> 15:31.680
That was my first wife, Jody.

15:33.558 --> 15:35.726
I know who it is. She was my mother.

15:35.810 --> 15:37.227
I know she was your mother.

15:37.645 --> 15:39.688
She was the most beautiful
woman in the world.

15:39.772 --> 15:41.356
She was the love of my life.

15:41.441 --> 15:42.899
She was the light of my love.

15:44.986 --> 15:48.530
I know if she was still alive
today, we'd be together.

15:49.949 --> 15:51.992
Such a tragic accident.

15:52.076 --> 15:54.202
What accident?

15:54.287 --> 15:56.663
The accident that cut her life short.

15:56.873 --> 15:59.750
It wasn't an accident. She left a note.

16:00.877 --> 16:02.878
Did it mention me?

16:04.505 --> 16:05.839
No.

16:06.883 --> 16:07.883
Ah.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.343
Not much of a letter writer, your mother.

16:11.262 --> 16:13.138
All right, Nicholas. Why
don't we get started.

16:14.682 --> 16:17.851
You can just take all this stuff
and throw it in a box.

16:17.935 --> 16:19.144
The paintings be careful of.

16:19.228 --> 16:21.063
Especially this one and that one,
and that one on the wall.

16:21.314 --> 16:24.566
Be careful of all this stuff.
It's all valuable.

16:25.526 --> 16:27.653
Nicholas, I want you to have this.

16:27.779 --> 16:29.905
This is an original Jackson Pollock.

16:29.989 --> 16:31.573
He was a friend.

16:31.658 --> 16:32.949
Oh, no. I couldn't.

16:33.034 --> 16:34.701
No, I want you to have it.

16:34.786 --> 16:36.745
Okay, thanks.

16:36.829 --> 16:38.538
Are you going to help move this
stuff, since it's yours?

16:38.623 --> 16:42.417
I wish I could, but I suffer from
lethal phlebitis in both legs.

16:42.502 --> 16:44.628
You be careful with those boxes.
There's manuscripts.

16:46.673 --> 16:48.882
Manuscripts.

16:49.050 --> 16:50.467
Those are your friends?

16:51.094 --> 16:52.177
I guess. Yeah.

16:52.261 --> 16:54.179
A homosexual and a black pothead?

16:54.263 --> 16:56.056
Well, good luck to you.

16:56.140 --> 16:58.183
Well, I have to get to work now.

16:58.267 --> 17:00.811
Do you mind just locking the padlock
when you're finished?

17:00.895 --> 17:02.688
Yeah. Wait. So you drive a taxi?

17:02.772 --> 17:04.189
Well, it's an excellent way of learning

17:04.272 --> 17:05.816
about all different kinds of people.

17:05.942 --> 17:07.233
And what is your vocation?

17:07.318 --> 17:09.111
My vocation? Uh...

17:09.444 --> 17:10.737
I've done lots of different jobs.

17:10.946 --> 17:13.115
I always thought you'd end up
a writer, like your old man.

17:13.199 --> 17:16.201
Actually, I do write. You
know, sometimes. I try.

17:16.285 --> 17:19.204
Well, there is no such thing
as trying to write.

17:19.288 --> 17:20.622
One writes, or one doesn't.

17:20.915 --> 17:23.750
You have to take every opportunity
to practice your craft.

17:24.292 --> 17:27.212
Anyway, I know you have inherited
some writing talent from me,

17:27.296 --> 17:28.839
because I am a truly great writer.

17:29.799 --> 17:30.882
I'm going to show you something.

17:35.179 --> 17:38.807
I have a letter from Viking Press.

17:39.183 --> 17:40.934
You've heard of Viking Press, haven't you?

17:41.018 --> 17:42.060
Yeah.

17:42.145 --> 17:44.271
Look at this. Look at that phrase there.

17:44.355 --> 17:47.649
"Your book is a virtuoso
display of personality.

17:49.193 --> 17:52.571
"Unfortunately, its dosage would kill
hardier readers than we have here."

17:52.655 --> 17:55.157
"Virtuoso display," Viking Press.

17:55.700 --> 17:58.827
Well, it's been a great
pleasure, Nicholas.

18:00.204 --> 18:01.455
Well, hey, uh...

18:02.206 --> 18:03.248
All right.

18:04.709 --> 18:08.003
You need anything? Aside from the Pollock?

18:08.463 --> 18:09.504
No.

18:10.173 --> 18:12.549
All right. Well, au revoir, then.

18:23.352 --> 18:24.394
You're welcome.

18:24.479 --> 18:25.896
Don't mention it.

18:28.566 --> 18:29.858
Your father's a nightmare.

18:31.110 --> 18:32.527
What's that?

18:32.987 --> 18:34.196
(LAUGHS)

18:34.363 --> 18:36.072
It's a fucking Jackson Pollock painting.

18:36.365 --> 18:38.366
Jackson Pollock? Jesus!

18:39.118 --> 18:40.202
Hmm.

18:41.370 --> 18:44.748
Pollock spelled his name
wrong when he signed it.

18:48.628 --> 18:50.170
NICK: So then he gives me a gift,

18:50.254 --> 18:52.172
a Jackson Pollock painting.

18:52.256 --> 18:54.549
Which, like an asshole, I think is real.

18:54.634 --> 18:56.176
So after 18 years of wondering,

18:56.260 --> 18:57.928
here's what I learned about my father.

18:58.012 --> 19:01.014
He's a racist, he's a homophobe,
and he's fucking crazy.

19:01.098 --> 19:04.309
Can you reach him? I mean,
if you wanted to?

19:04.393 --> 19:06.478
I don't know that I ever want
to see him again. Really.

19:07.688 --> 19:08.897
I don't know how I feel about it.

19:08.981 --> 19:12.192
I can't really locate what I feel.

19:12.276 --> 19:13.443
Is that why you called me?

19:13.694 --> 19:15.320
To help you locate your feelings?

19:15.488 --> 19:19.199
Do you want to get out of
here? You look beautiful.

19:19.283 --> 19:20.826
None of that. We're friends now.

19:20.910 --> 19:22.369
We're friends?

19:22.453 --> 19:23.495
Yeah.

19:23.871 --> 19:26.039
I mean, don't get me wrong, I enjoyed
sleeping with you, but...

19:26.249 --> 19:27.249
Thank you.

19:27.333 --> 19:28.416
I told you I didn't want a relationship.

19:28.626 --> 19:30.752
So, now we're friends.

19:31.587 --> 19:34.422
Okay. Well, thanks for letting me know.

19:35.216 --> 19:36.758
You're welcome.

19:39.846 --> 19:42.389
You should think about working
at Harbor Street.

19:43.266 --> 19:44.641
Why?

19:44.725 --> 19:46.309
Well, I was in kind of a fucked state,

19:46.394 --> 19:47.936
mentally, when I started there.

19:48.980 --> 19:51.648
Um, yeah, just, I like working there.

19:55.278 --> 19:57.779
Tell me about your fucked state.

20:00.783 --> 20:03.034
Do you want another one of these?

20:13.921 --> 20:15.338
All right?

20:16.632 --> 20:19.050
Hey, how are you? How's it going?

20:34.150 --> 20:35.609
How did you hear about this job?

20:36.569 --> 20:39.321
A friend of mine, Denise, works here.

20:39.405 --> 20:40.447
Okay.

20:41.949 --> 20:43.992
So what makes you want to
work with the homeless?

20:45.703 --> 20:47.245
I don't know. Uh...

20:50.166 --> 20:53.460
I mean, we are put on this Earth
to help other people, right?

20:53.544 --> 20:55.295
Someone I knew told me that.

20:55.379 --> 20:56.379
Who?

20:56.839 --> 20:59.591
Who? No one. Uh...

20:59.675 --> 21:02.802
Look, I guess I just see homeless
people everywhere.

21:02.887 --> 21:04.888
It seems like there is more and more.

21:05.765 --> 21:06.806
Seems like it.

21:08.684 --> 21:11.603
I guess I just want a job that,
you know, means something.

21:11.687 --> 21:14.940
Something where I don't despise myself
when I come home from work.

21:15.024 --> 21:16.524
So you despise yourself?

21:18.444 --> 21:21.196
I don't know. Uh, sure. Doesn't everyone?

21:21.280 --> 21:22.864
I don't despise myself.

21:24.200 --> 21:25.617
I used to be a guest here.

21:26.327 --> 21:29.871
Then I worked here. I had a permanent bed.

21:29.956 --> 21:31.706
And then I moved out.

21:31.791 --> 21:35.293
I got a job in construction,
became the foreman.

21:35.378 --> 21:37.379
Then one day I came back here
to give something back.

21:37.463 --> 21:38.964
So I've come a long way up,

21:39.048 --> 21:40.382
but it's a quick fall down.

21:40.466 --> 21:42.884
So I really can't afford to hate myself.

21:42.969 --> 21:44.469
You know what I'm talking about?

21:49.517 --> 21:50.850
You don't know what I'm talking about.

21:51.560 --> 21:53.561
But that's okay.

21:54.730 --> 21:58.400
Tell you what. I can put
you on the fill-in list.

21:58.484 --> 22:01.903
If we need somebody to
fill in, we'll call.

22:02.321 --> 22:03.947
Thanks.

22:06.784 --> 22:10.245
Hey, so why do they call you Captain?

22:11.580 --> 22:13.123
Because I'm the Captain.

22:14.750 --> 22:16.209
Okay.

22:18.587 --> 22:19.587
IVAN: Just bring it by right now.

22:20.464 --> 22:21.881
Okay, later.

22:22.258 --> 22:24.259
Hey, they called from Harbor Street Inn.

22:24.343 --> 22:26.344
They want you to fill in tonight.

22:27.513 --> 22:29.014
Tonight?

22:37.148 --> 22:39.399
NICK: There were different types
of people who worked there.

22:39.483 --> 22:40.859
There were the religious types.

22:40.943 --> 22:43.028
I want to live my life
the way Christ does.

22:43.112 --> 22:45.363
Also, I hate my rich parents.

22:45.448 --> 22:46.531
Hey, guys, can you bring those over here?

22:46.615 --> 22:47.615
There were the punks.

22:47.700 --> 22:50.160
Check in, sir, and we are gonna
get you to the clinic.

22:50.244 --> 22:51.286
This place is hardcore.

22:51.370 --> 22:53.163
Plus, the pay is not bad. Next.

22:53.247 --> 22:54.372
There were the ex-cons.

22:54.457 --> 22:57.625
All right, next. So this dude
was gonna shoot me, right?

22:57.710 --> 23:00.336
So, I turned sideways, 'cause
that is what you do.

23:00.421 --> 23:02.839
You turn sideways, you take it in the arm.

23:02.923 --> 23:05.550
I flex my bicep, I take the bullet.

23:05.634 --> 23:10.263
And then I grabbed the gun from this
guy, and I'm like bam-bam-bam-bam.

23:10.347 --> 23:12.974
Right in his fucking head, then
it's like click-click-click.

23:14.060 --> 23:17.312
Let me tell you, I had to disappear
for a while after that.

23:17.396 --> 23:18.855
All right, put your arms up.

23:18.939 --> 23:20.482
Joy was an ex-cokehead and a prostitute.

23:20.566 --> 23:21.608
JOY: There you go, honey.

23:21.692 --> 23:23.735
Now, she's like a mother to the guys.

23:23.819 --> 23:25.070
Unfortunately, in a couple of years,

23:25.154 --> 23:27.405
she will be sitting in a room with
a shotgun across her lap,

23:27.490 --> 23:30.241
back to dealing and smoking crack 24/7.

23:30.326 --> 23:32.494
It's hard to stay changed.

23:34.663 --> 23:37.290
I start out working inside the
cage handing out bed tickets,

23:37.374 --> 23:40.543
collecting people's valuables and
locking them up overnight.

23:41.003 --> 23:43.421
It's Friday, payday. A lot
of the guests have jobs.

23:43.506 --> 23:46.007
There is more money to slip
into the envelopes.

23:46.884 --> 23:47.926
Let's go. Hey!

23:48.010 --> 23:49.761
The air is thick, stale,
smells like sweat.

23:49.845 --> 23:51.221
Back off.

23:51.305 --> 23:52.722
Friday, the drunks are more boisterous.

23:52.848 --> 23:54.974
MAN 1: Move up, old man! MAN 2: Why
you always got to be touching me?

23:55.059 --> 23:56.768
Because you are standing
still, that's why.

23:56.852 --> 23:59.562
Every single day, I get in line,
and you're right up my ass.

23:59.855 --> 24:01.231
(ARGUING INDISTINCTLY)

24:01.524 --> 24:02.524
Maybe I should help.

24:02.608 --> 24:04.234
Yeah, maybe not. Not yet.

24:04.902 --> 24:06.236
(CONTINUES ARGUING)

24:06.695 --> 24:08.446
There is a balance between
escalating and defusing.

24:08.697 --> 24:11.282
Knowing when to step in,
and when to back off.

24:11.367 --> 24:12.867
Hey, buddy, calm down!

24:13.702 --> 24:15.120
Oh, shit.

24:15.204 --> 24:16.704
I don't know that balance yet.

24:16.789 --> 24:18.498
Well? Are you able to locate
your feelings now?

24:18.582 --> 24:20.208
Yeah, this fucking hurts.

24:20.292 --> 24:21.626
You are going to have a good shiner.

24:21.710 --> 24:23.586
You didn't tell me this
place was such a rush.

24:23.671 --> 24:26.923
It's addictive. Watch out,
or you will never leave.

24:27.550 --> 24:29.968
So, how many of these people
get back on their feet?

24:30.052 --> 24:31.511
I couldn't tell you.

24:31.595 --> 24:33.721
But what I do know is a year from now,

24:33.806 --> 24:37.767
100-150 of the guys who come
through here will be dead.

24:37.852 --> 24:41.271
We catch them on the way down.
Next stop, the morgue.

24:47.778 --> 24:48.987
(DOORBELL RINGS)

24:52.908 --> 24:53.908
(CHUCKLING)

24:53.993 --> 24:56.202
Hey. Steady Ray, as ever.

24:56.370 --> 24:57.704
Jonathan, how are you?

24:57.788 --> 25:00.206
So, I thought I might stay over tonight.

25:00.291 --> 25:03.459
I find myself momentarily between places.

25:03.544 --> 25:06.921
The thing is, Claire's mom is
here. She's staying with us.

25:07.006 --> 25:09.299
That is okay. I'll sleep on the couch.

25:09.383 --> 25:10.925
No, that is where she's staying.

25:11.010 --> 25:12.677
We are renovating the guest room.

25:12.761 --> 25:15.305
Tell her to get the fuck off
and let me sleep with her.

25:15.681 --> 25:16.764
Is she nice?

25:16.891 --> 25:17.974
Yeah. You met her?

25:18.058 --> 25:19.517
(SINGING) Mother-in-law, mother-in-law

25:19.602 --> 25:20.852
Mother-in-law

25:20.936 --> 25:22.353
Hey, honey!

25:22.438 --> 25:23.438
Shh.

25:26.108 --> 25:27.942
I mean, this wasn't because of the old

25:28.027 --> 25:29.485
burning-of-the-Christmas-tree
thing, was it?

25:29.570 --> 25:31.279
No. That's ancient history.

25:31.488 --> 25:34.824
Exactly, because it was really funny.
You got to admit, it was.

25:34.909 --> 25:36.659
Yeah. That was a lot of fun.

25:37.286 --> 25:40.413
Sure, all right. Well, okay,
give Claire de Lune my love.

25:40.497 --> 25:42.290
And I'm going to try Dugan.

25:43.459 --> 25:44.918
He is always begging me to come over

25:45.002 --> 25:46.419
and provide some free entertainment for

25:46.503 --> 25:47.879
him and his miserable missus.

25:48.172 --> 25:49.464
Dugan moved to Florida.

25:49.548 --> 25:51.424
He did? Moved to Florida? Why
the hell would he do that?

25:51.508 --> 25:52.926
I don't know, the weather.

25:53.010 --> 25:54.761
Oh, the weather.

25:54.845 --> 25:57.180
Okay, looks like I'm going to
head to my suite at the Ritz.

25:57.973 --> 25:59.390
I'm sorry. Okay, Ray.

25:59.475 --> 26:00.892
Good night. All right. Good night.

26:02.269 --> 26:03.645
Take care. Give the lovely missus my love.

26:03.729 --> 26:04.771
Don't forget to write.

26:05.064 --> 26:07.857
Yeah, I'll write. In jail.

26:07.983 --> 26:09.067
(CHUCKLES)

26:12.154 --> 26:13.571
CLAIRE: Ray?

26:13.906 --> 26:14.989
I'm coming.

26:31.215 --> 26:34.133
JONATHAN: For the next few weeks
I lived out of my cab.

26:35.302 --> 26:38.471
Renting it 24 hours a day,
seven days a week.

26:41.267 --> 26:43.434
It's a wonderful life.

26:47.481 --> 26:49.899
You shit at the bus station,

26:50.025 --> 26:52.193
you shower at the Y.

26:52.278 --> 26:53.778
But it's not all fun and games.

26:53.862 --> 26:55.822
Cabbies get shot in the head every night.

26:56.031 --> 26:58.866
Bamo! Right in the jugular. Right
in the fucking jugular.

26:58.951 --> 27:02.203
I'll ram it down their throat and
rip their insides right out.

27:10.212 --> 27:11.796
Hurry up!

27:45.998 --> 27:47.081
(THUDDING)

27:49.001 --> 27:50.251
(SIREN BLARING)

27:50.753 --> 27:53.463
The police said I hit someone,
or some fucking thing.

27:55.299 --> 27:57.258
What can I say to that?

28:01.138 --> 28:04.682
Now, I have no license, no
cab, no place to sleep.

28:04.767 --> 28:08.353
Perhaps I'll start a new book,
Memoirs of a Moron!

28:08.437 --> 28:14.984
Memoirs of a fucking moron.

28:26.455 --> 28:28.623
NICK: After the cage, I work housing.

28:28.707 --> 28:31.626
It's more intense. You are not
protected behind steel mesh.

28:33.128 --> 28:35.713
Okay, grab a cup, have a good shower.

28:38.675 --> 28:40.385
Hey, I'll meet you in the
hot room in 10 minutes.

28:40.469 --> 28:41.511
Okay. If I'm not there,

28:41.595 --> 28:43.012
just take your clothes off
and start without me.

28:43.097 --> 28:44.555
Okay.

28:44.681 --> 28:48.267
The hot room smells of superheated
sweat, quick fermented.

29:14.044 --> 29:15.503
Excuse me.

29:15.671 --> 29:17.004
I need a new pair of pants.

29:26.974 --> 29:29.350
No problem. I'll be right back.

29:36.358 --> 29:39.485
Hey, how do I know what size he wears?

29:40.028 --> 29:41.654
You ask him.

29:42.364 --> 29:45.283
At Harbor Street you write up every
day's events in the log,

29:45.367 --> 29:47.702
and you read off your entry that night.

29:47.786 --> 29:49.370
He's not gonna bite.

29:49.455 --> 29:52.206
I take that opportunity to practice.

29:52.291 --> 29:56.961
"9: 10, Isaac Clegg fell out of
bed, and the bed fell on him.

29:57.796 --> 29:59.839
"The skin of a drunk splits open easily,

29:59.923 --> 30:03.342
"their blood flows more freely,
thinned out by the booze.

30:03.760 --> 30:05.344
"The nurse is gone for the evening

30:05.429 --> 30:07.805
"and Isaac is loath to go to the hospital.

30:07.890 --> 30:09.849
"I make an attempt to bandage him."

30:10.684 --> 30:15.563
I'm just gonna wrap this
around you. You okay?

30:16.648 --> 30:20.109
"9:30, I was able to convince George D.

30:20.194 --> 30:22.487
"To sit still for his monthly de-lousing."

30:22.613 --> 30:27.825
My beloved family, they beheaded
me, their beloved Queen.

30:28.535 --> 30:30.995
I loved them. They were my friends.

30:31.163 --> 30:33.247
"Lice thrive so well on George's body

30:33.332 --> 30:36.292
"that they can be seen crawling
over him at 20 paces."

30:36.376 --> 30:37.710
I would never hurt them.

30:38.086 --> 30:39.253
I would never kill them.

30:40.756 --> 30:44.133
Hey, it's okay, man. I understand, George.

30:44.218 --> 30:48.804
But, I mean, they beheaded you,
didn't they? So why not?

30:55.729 --> 30:57.355
This is the right decision, George.

30:57.606 --> 31:00.816
"Nothing in the shelter makes
me understand my purpose more

31:00.901 --> 31:03.653
"than to kill bugs off of a
homeless man's flesh..."

31:06.114 --> 31:07.657
Okay. All right.

31:08.075 --> 31:09.200
Let's get you cleaned up.

31:09.284 --> 31:13.538
"...to dress him well in donated,
cast-off clothes,

31:13.622 --> 31:18.084
"and to see him the next day laughing
beside a burning barrel."

31:22.422 --> 31:25.174
Okay, Nick. Very expressive.

31:25.300 --> 31:28.970
I like the stuff about Isaac being
loath to go to the hospital.

31:29.054 --> 31:30.680
Thank you.

31:31.139 --> 31:34.308
How about we let the next
person read their entry?

31:39.731 --> 31:43.067
"10:00 p.m., fight broke
out in reading area.

31:43.151 --> 31:45.736
"10:30, Wally G. Caught smoking in bed."

31:45.821 --> 31:47.572
Which I confiscated, by the way.

31:47.656 --> 31:49.949
Lucky number 41.

31:50.033 --> 31:51.951
Hey, what are you up to after work?

31:52.244 --> 31:53.452
Nothing.

31:55.831 --> 31:56.872
Thank you.

31:59.751 --> 32:01.419
I thought we were just friends.

32:01.503 --> 32:03.254
DENISE: Shut up.

32:08.093 --> 32:09.802
What's all this?

32:11.096 --> 32:12.221
Just old letters.

32:12.306 --> 32:13.681
Is this from your father?

32:15.684 --> 32:16.851
He was in jail?

32:17.519 --> 32:19.020
He passed forged checks

32:19.855 --> 32:22.732
in between writing the
great American novel.

32:23.358 --> 32:24.567
Nice.

32:28.655 --> 32:30.531
Are these all from your dad?

32:31.783 --> 32:32.867
Yeah.

32:35.037 --> 32:37.747
There's like a hundred letters in here.

32:46.882 --> 32:48.007
This yours?

32:48.091 --> 32:49.383
Don't read that.

32:50.510 --> 32:51.719
"Loaded, I say.

32:52.429 --> 32:56.891
"Wasted, looped, lit, off my ass,
befuddled, reeling, tanked,

32:57.225 --> 33:00.394
"punch-drunk, mean drunk,
maintenance drunk,

33:01.563 --> 33:05.274
"sloppy drunk, happy drunk, weepy
drunk, blind drunk, dead drunk,

33:05.525 --> 33:07.735
"serious drinker, hard drinker."

33:10.739 --> 33:12.239
What is this?

33:14.743 --> 33:17.703
Nothing. Some poetry. It's shit.

33:18.038 --> 33:19.997
"Polluted, blitzed, shattered, zonked,

33:20.082 --> 33:22.375
"ossified, annihilated, fossilized,

33:22.459 --> 33:25.753
"stinko, blotto, legless, smashed, soaked,

33:26.672 --> 33:28.714
"screwed, blasted,

33:29.132 --> 33:33.219
"hammered, tore up, ripped
up, ripped, destroyed."

33:35.597 --> 33:37.139
Cheerful stuff.

33:37.224 --> 33:38.516
No one will ever read it.

33:39.184 --> 33:40.267
I just did.

33:41.895 --> 33:43.104
Come back to bed.

33:46.483 --> 33:48.401
What will you give me if I do?

34:12.467 --> 34:14.135
JONATHAN: Dear Mr. President.

34:14.219 --> 34:16.469
The proper study of mankind is man.

34:17.054 --> 34:22.143
Ortega y Gasset defined genius as the
ability to invent one's occupation.

34:22.226 --> 34:24.770
I am a writer, a poet, a storyteller.

34:24.855 --> 34:27.898
WOMAN: (OVER INTERCOM) The library
will be closing in 10 minutes.

34:28.775 --> 34:32.402
The library will be closing in 10 minutes.

34:32.487 --> 34:35.156
If the present holds any promise
of the years ahead,

34:35.239 --> 34:37.867
the United States can look forward
to many generations of

34:37.993 --> 34:40.786
executives unable to spell
their names correctly.

34:40.871 --> 34:43.664
Yours, as ever, Jonathan R. Flynn.

34:47.960 --> 34:51.505
Give me that. That's my personal
property, you ape.

34:58.013 --> 34:59.138
Thank you.

35:01.767 --> 35:04.560
Tonight, I'm doing a little
after-hours banking.

35:04.644 --> 35:08.314
I'm depositing a check for $750,000,

35:08.398 --> 35:10.441
an advance for my novel The Button Man.

35:12.194 --> 35:13.486
It's classic.

35:15.238 --> 35:17.573
They're making a movie,
a movie of my life.

35:18.033 --> 35:19.116
Excuse me?

35:19.201 --> 35:20.451
They're making a movie.

35:20.535 --> 35:22.244
Someone, behind the wall.

35:22.412 --> 35:23.829
They are?

35:23.914 --> 35:26.457
Who in living hell would want to
make a movie about your life?

35:26.541 --> 35:29.710
That would be one boring, redundant,
piece of shit movie.

35:56.696 --> 35:57.905
Here you go.

36:00.784 --> 36:02.243
You have to take it outside, Eric.

36:16.883 --> 36:18.092
Oh, what a pleasant surprise. Thank you.

36:18.176 --> 36:19.218
You're welcome.

36:19.594 --> 36:20.636
Dawn of a new day.

36:20.720 --> 36:21.762
I like that.

36:22.264 --> 36:23.973
I'm going to write a poem about you, Dawn.

36:24.057 --> 36:25.724
You are too sweet.

36:26.017 --> 36:27.852
Cheers. Cheers.

36:31.606 --> 36:34.191
Dawn. Sawn...

36:34.985 --> 36:36.277
(MUTTERS INDISTINCTLY)

37:14.900 --> 37:15.983
(GRUNTING)

37:50.769 --> 37:54.772
NICK: He's seen this before. Bums
sprawled out from drinking.

37:54.856 --> 37:58.150
But he has never actually
stood over the blowers,

37:58.234 --> 38:01.153
let the hot air seep into his clothes.

38:01.237 --> 38:02.863
The air is sucked out of the library.

38:02.948 --> 38:06.617
Even on the coldest nights there
is too much heat inside.

38:07.744 --> 38:09.578
It's another prison, these blowers.

38:09.704 --> 38:12.456
Because once you have landed,
you can't leave.

38:12.540 --> 38:16.460
Because one step off the blower
is cold, hypothermia cold,

38:16.544 --> 38:18.921
now that you are sodden with steam.

38:19.005 --> 38:22.383
The blower is a room of
heat with no walls.

38:25.428 --> 38:29.306
My father is an invisible man,
in an invisible room,

38:29.391 --> 38:31.642
in the invisible city.

38:41.027 --> 38:42.152
Whoo!

38:50.787 --> 38:52.454
I really appreciate the help, sir.

38:52.539 --> 38:54.456
Call me Carlos. Okay. Carlos.

38:54.874 --> 38:57.042
So, Jerry, how many nights
have you been homeless?

38:57.127 --> 38:59.795
Just one night. One bad night
with the wife, boy.

38:59.879 --> 39:00.879
That is all it takes, one bad night.

39:00.964 --> 39:01.964
You got that right.

39:02.048 --> 39:03.757
What is up, Nick?

39:03.925 --> 39:07.428
MAN: For the new guys, no
bottles or weapons, okay?

39:07.512 --> 39:09.221
All right, you're good.

39:09.347 --> 39:12.683
Stretch your arms out for me,
sir. Please? Thank you.

39:14.769 --> 39:16.770
All right. Step up.

39:24.446 --> 39:27.406
I'd like a room for the evening.

39:27.949 --> 39:29.283
You want a bed?

39:29.534 --> 39:30.576
That'll do for now.

39:32.328 --> 39:34.538
Well, this is a pleasant surprise.

39:34.622 --> 39:36.081
So, you're employed here now?

39:36.875 --> 39:38.625
Yes, I'm employed here.

39:39.169 --> 39:41.962
Well, I approve. We are put on this
Earth to help other people.

39:44.090 --> 39:45.966
You must be gathering some
excellent material.

39:46.051 --> 39:49.303
MAN: Hey. You giving out tickets, or what?

39:56.978 --> 39:58.437
Many thanks.

39:58.521 --> 40:01.440
And if a private room does
open up, I'd be grateful.

40:13.411 --> 40:14.703
Hey, what's up?

40:14.788 --> 40:16.246
My father is here.

40:16.331 --> 40:18.165
What? My father, he's here.

40:18.249 --> 40:20.751
He's staying here, he is a guest tonight.

40:20.835 --> 40:21.835
Jesus.

40:21.920 --> 40:22.961
CARLOS: Oh, shit.

40:23.421 --> 40:25.380
Your dad is sleeping here.
Your own father.

40:25.673 --> 40:27.966
Nick, man, you are the
unluckiest guy I know.

40:28.051 --> 40:30.469
Thanks, Carlos. Just keep it
to yourself, man. Please?

40:30.553 --> 40:31.804
No worries.

40:47.278 --> 40:49.488
Hey, Nick. You feel like
going home tonight?

40:49.572 --> 40:51.031
No. Why?

40:52.367 --> 40:54.243
Because your father is here.

40:55.203 --> 40:56.286
So you heard about that.

40:56.371 --> 40:57.454
Yeah.

40:57.539 --> 40:59.081
Who else knows?

40:59.165 --> 41:00.874
We are with you, man.

41:00.959 --> 41:02.543
Fucking Carlos.

41:02.710 --> 41:05.254
Maybe you could take the night off.
You know, I can get a fill-in.

41:05.338 --> 41:07.131
No.

41:07.215 --> 41:10.008
It's my job. I work here.

41:27.819 --> 41:28.861
Let's go.

41:28.987 --> 41:30.070
Come with me.

41:43.501 --> 41:44.877
Bottom bunk.

42:16.951 --> 42:17.993
JONATHAN: Nicholas.

42:34.302 --> 42:36.303
Interesting view.

42:38.139 --> 42:40.849
I thought you were staying
at a friend's place?

42:40.934 --> 42:42.559
A couple of things fell through.

42:42.644 --> 42:44.269
I was bunking in my cab for a while,

42:44.354 --> 42:46.271
but that is no longer possible.

42:46.356 --> 42:48.273
So I have been sleeping alfresco.

42:48.650 --> 42:52.069
Alfresco? You mean outside? For how long?

42:54.405 --> 42:55.989
Three weeks or so.

42:57.033 --> 43:00.786
Don't look so grave. This is
a great opportunity for me.

43:01.037 --> 43:02.246
What opportunity?

43:03.122 --> 43:05.249
The opportunity to freeze to death?

43:05.333 --> 43:08.001
The opportunity to see how
the other half lives.

43:08.086 --> 43:10.462
The poor, the downtrodden.

43:10.546 --> 43:13.298
I'm doing the same thing here as
you are, gathering material.

43:13.508 --> 43:17.177
No, I'm not gathering material.
This is my life.

43:17.428 --> 43:19.221
Life is gathering material.

43:20.974 --> 43:24.559
I like that. Help me remember that.

43:25.103 --> 43:26.979
They won't even let me bring
a goddamned pen up here.

43:27.063 --> 43:28.188
Can't you do anything about that?

43:28.982 --> 43:30.607
No. Don't you have any clout around here?

43:31.276 --> 43:32.567
Sorry.

43:32.652 --> 43:36.655
Well, anyway, my writing is going
extremely well, by the by.

43:37.407 --> 43:40.617
I'm already almost done with
my revisions to Chapter 37.

43:41.369 --> 43:44.288
Perhaps I'll let you read
it someday. It's classic.

43:44.414 --> 43:46.415
Okay, look, you can't stay here. Why not?

43:47.000 --> 43:48.292
Because I work here.

43:49.460 --> 43:52.170
Well, don't worry. This is only
a very temporary situation.

43:52.255 --> 43:54.298
I don't want to disrupt
your life in the least.

43:54.382 --> 43:56.591
I have a friend of mine who's begging
me to move down to Florida.

43:56.676 --> 43:58.885
He has a guest house and
a job there for me.

43:59.012 --> 44:01.555
Okay. Florida, that sounds great.

44:02.223 --> 44:03.390
In the meantime,

44:03.474 --> 44:05.017
this is an excellent opportunity for

44:05.101 --> 44:06.643
you and I to make up for lost time.

44:07.395 --> 44:09.896
Destiny has brought us together
for one fleeting moment.

44:11.065 --> 44:13.358
Let us not spit in its eye.

44:23.369 --> 44:24.578
IVAN: Thank you again, man.

44:24.662 --> 44:26.330
And you know, let me know if
that shit don't work out.

44:26.414 --> 44:27.372
Let me know, all right?

44:27.457 --> 44:28.498
MAN: Okay. We'll see you.

44:28.583 --> 44:29.666
All right.

44:32.253 --> 44:34.546
I mean, you could ask him to
stay here for a few days.

44:34.964 --> 44:36.131
No, he can't.

44:37.008 --> 44:38.508
I don't even know if the
Florida thing is real.

44:38.843 --> 44:40.427
I hope so, for your sake.

44:42.305 --> 44:43.513
Just weed, right?

44:44.057 --> 44:45.098
Excuse me?

44:45.183 --> 44:46.808
You're only selling weed, right?

44:47.143 --> 44:48.769
Yeah, just weed.

44:48.853 --> 44:50.854
I'm just saying, he's your father.

44:51.439 --> 44:52.564
Uh...

44:52.940 --> 44:54.066
I've had father figures.

44:55.276 --> 44:58.111
All right, Nick! Keep
your eye on the ball.

44:58.946 --> 45:00.614
They were all burned up.

45:02.367 --> 45:04.993
It's amazing what can happen
to the human body, Nick.

45:06.829 --> 45:08.330
Hey! What the hell are you showing him?

45:08.414 --> 45:10.123
Hey, sweetie. What the fuck, Travis?

45:10.792 --> 45:12.876
Pick that up! Come on,
I want to talk to you.

45:22.512 --> 45:24.471
I thought he was a little young
to be driving a car.

45:24.764 --> 45:26.473
You could have killed
yourself. Get inside!

45:28.726 --> 45:29.810
Thank you very much.

45:30.186 --> 45:31.561
You're welcome.

45:32.188 --> 45:33.480
Have a good day. You, too.

45:37.985 --> 45:40.404
My mom had a lot of different
boyfriends, growing up.

45:40.488 --> 45:43.865
Come on, buddy. Good job.

46:06.305 --> 46:08.014
But I never had a father.

46:13.688 --> 46:14.855
Luckily, I had a mother.

46:14.981 --> 46:18.024
Hey, who you playing ball with?

46:18.317 --> 46:20.402
Nobody. Myself.

46:21.988 --> 46:23.238
Get your mitt.

46:23.322 --> 46:25.991
Honey, I'm exhausted.

46:27.743 --> 46:28.869
Okay.

46:30.538 --> 46:31.788
All right.

46:33.124 --> 46:35.000
Let me get my mitt. Heads up!

46:35.376 --> 46:36.877
Good one. Thanks.

46:37.003 --> 46:38.837
I'll be right back. Okay.

46:55.062 --> 46:57.022
You are not listening
to me. I'm listening.

46:57.106 --> 46:59.941
He stole $30 from me!

47:00.026 --> 47:01.526
I understand that. Hey, Nick!

47:01.611 --> 47:03.153
Jonathan asked me to give
this letter to you, man.

47:03.237 --> 47:05.071
So he's some kind of famous writer?

47:05.156 --> 47:07.657
Yeah, that's why he's staying
at Harbor Street.

47:09.785 --> 47:13.455
JONATHAN: Dear Nick, many deep
thanks for your warm welcome.

47:13.539 --> 47:15.415
I must say you seemed anxious.

47:15.500 --> 47:17.626
Of course, writers, especially poets,

47:17.710 --> 47:19.753
are particularly prone to madness.

47:19.837 --> 47:21.254
Hey, babe.

47:21.589 --> 47:23.089
Okay.

47:23.174 --> 47:25.550
There exists a striking association

47:25.635 --> 47:27.969
between creativity and manic depression.

47:28.638 --> 47:32.098
The only important thing, though,
is to simply do the work.

47:34.435 --> 47:40.232
It's not a sharp pain, it's a dull
pain. I haven't eaten in two days.

47:45.112 --> 47:47.280
Hey, straight through the
back, down the stairs.

48:01.754 --> 48:03.088
JONATHAN: Most of these guys here are

48:03.172 --> 48:06.174
a bunch of fucking deadbeat
panhandlers and pederasts.

48:06.259 --> 48:08.635
These perverts, they wouldn't last
a second in federal prison.

48:09.011 --> 48:13.139
They are all homosexuals. I despise
homosexuals, and they despise me.

48:13.224 --> 48:15.350
I know what I'm talking about.
I talk the straight talk.

48:15.434 --> 48:17.686
I wasn't locked up in federal
prison with choirboys,

48:17.770 --> 48:19.271
that's for sure. JODY: Next, please.

48:33.244 --> 48:34.995
Thank you.

48:36.622 --> 48:37.831
Hey.

48:37.915 --> 48:38.957
Hi.

48:39.041 --> 48:40.667
See this? Uh-huh.

48:41.043 --> 48:42.794
Don't ever become a writer.

49:18.372 --> 49:20.665
Just around the corner to the
right, follow the hallway.

49:20.750 --> 49:21.791
You know where to go.

49:21.876 --> 49:22.834
Jesus. Hey, what happened to you?

49:22.918 --> 49:23.918
I'm fine.

49:24.003 --> 49:25.211
You're fine? You should get to the clinic.

49:25.296 --> 49:28.423
You should see the other cocksuckers.
This is nothing.

49:28.507 --> 49:31.468
By the way, I have a little gift for you.

49:31.552 --> 49:33.678
From one writer to another.

50:02.708 --> 50:04.584
Is there a tailor here?

50:04.669 --> 50:06.127
No.

50:06.504 --> 50:07.796
I'm going to need a new coat.

50:08.673 --> 50:09.839
Okay.

50:22.937 --> 50:24.354
All right, so I won't be there.

50:24.438 --> 50:26.439
But I'll get there next time, okay?

50:27.441 --> 50:28.650
All right.

50:28.984 --> 50:30.068
Hey.

50:31.445 --> 50:34.030
You are not just selling weed, right?

50:40.162 --> 50:42.831
Watch your hands. Watch your hands.

50:42.915 --> 50:44.541
Why should a truly great writer

50:44.625 --> 50:46.459
be subjected to these fucking indignities?

50:51.882 --> 50:53.299
There we go.

50:54.677 --> 50:55.760
JONATHAN: What are you doing?
That's my property.

50:55.845 --> 50:56.845
Come on, get out of here.

50:56.929 --> 50:58.513
That's my property. That's my property.

50:58.597 --> 50:59.597
Fucking homo.

50:59.682 --> 51:00.807
Calm down. Calm down, now.

51:00.891 --> 51:02.976
I'm going to transform this
cesspool of a world.

51:03.060 --> 51:05.645
I'm going to transform it
with a fucking word!

51:10.317 --> 51:12.819
You know, he is not going anywhere.

51:12.903 --> 51:14.571
It's been weeks.

51:16.157 --> 51:18.575
What do you suggest I do about it?

51:19.869 --> 51:21.870
Get a job somewhere else?

51:26.083 --> 51:27.250
Hey,

51:28.669 --> 51:30.670
you want to do some blow?

51:30.963 --> 51:32.005
Um...

51:32.590 --> 51:34.132
I despise blow.

51:34.800 --> 51:37.177
Turns people into fucking scumbags.

51:38.095 --> 51:40.430
But you go ahead if you want to.

51:42.349 --> 51:45.393
GABRIEL: 12:30, Floyd Perkins
reports physical altercation.

51:45.478 --> 51:46.853
Report completed.

51:46.937 --> 51:50.315
2:00 a.m., shift change. Brian
gets permission to sign out.

51:50.399 --> 51:52.609
7:00 p.m., Jon Flynn was caught

51:52.693 --> 51:54.068
trying to smuggle a bottle in tonight.

51:54.153 --> 51:57.071
At first he was abusive, but he calmed
down and was given a warning.

51:57.156 --> 51:58.615
He wasn't put out for the night?

52:01.702 --> 52:02.952
It's cold out there, man.

52:03.704 --> 52:06.790
He asked me to give a letter to you.

52:13.214 --> 52:14.339
JONATHAN: Nick,

52:15.090 --> 52:17.467
I thought last evening at Harbor Street,

52:17.551 --> 52:19.469
waiting for 8:00 p.m. To come...

52:19.553 --> 52:22.847
I thought if your very beautiful
mother were alive,

52:22.932 --> 52:25.600
and if she could somehow see this scene,

52:25.684 --> 52:27.769
her son at work and his father a resident

52:27.853 --> 52:30.980
at Harbor Street shelter for the homeless.

52:33.400 --> 52:36.986
The beaten, the sad, the losers
in life's great game.

52:37.947 --> 52:41.699
Jody would have laughed loudly
at the entire macabre scene.

52:48.207 --> 52:52.544
She was the most beautiful
woman in the world.

52:57.091 --> 52:59.217
She was the love of my life.

53:01.512 --> 53:03.304
The light of my love.

53:05.391 --> 53:08.893
If she were here today, she
would be with me now.

53:12.940 --> 53:14.440
What happened

53:16.527 --> 53:18.570
to my face?

53:19.572 --> 53:21.489
I'm only 28 years old.

53:23.409 --> 53:25.159
Why do I look like this?

53:25.244 --> 53:26.911
Excuse me? What happened to me?

53:26.996 --> 53:29.581
What happened! What have you done to me?

53:29.665 --> 53:30.915
What have you done to me?

53:31.000 --> 53:34.127
COUNSELOR: He kept shouting at
me that he was 28 years old,

53:34.211 --> 53:37.630
and it just... It kind of freaked
me out, and I just...

53:38.591 --> 53:40.008
What are you looking at?

53:41.510 --> 53:42.719
Nothing.

53:42.803 --> 53:43.928
I'm sorry.

53:44.013 --> 53:45.722
Don't be sorry. Sorry for what?

53:47.933 --> 53:49.934
That it freaked you out?

53:50.019 --> 53:51.185
It's nothing.

53:51.270 --> 53:52.604
Wait until you have been
here a few months.

53:52.688 --> 53:54.063
Easy, Nick. Take it easy.

53:54.148 --> 53:55.899
I am taking it easy.

53:57.651 --> 54:00.153
This isn't me we are talking about.

54:00.696 --> 54:01.863
CAPTAIN: No, it's not.

54:05.367 --> 54:06.409
Go ahead.

54:08.746 --> 54:13.541
11: 15, tables and chairs put away
in the gym from overflow.

54:32.686 --> 54:35.021
Did you read my last letter?

54:36.815 --> 54:37.857
Yes.

54:39.818 --> 54:41.277
Beautifully written, wasn't it?

54:42.696 --> 54:44.447
Don't write to me about my fucking mother.

54:44.531 --> 54:46.282
Your fucking mother?

54:47.034 --> 54:50.662
Your fucking mother? How dare
you refer to her that way.

54:50.746 --> 54:53.498
How dare you say, "How dare you," to me.

54:53.958 --> 54:56.626
Well, let me rephrase it. Don't fucking
write to me about my mother.

54:56.710 --> 55:00.046
It only makes you sound childish
using profanity like that.

55:00.130 --> 55:03.132
Sorry, you don't get to
patronize me. Okay?

55:03.217 --> 55:05.426
You don't get to pretend to be my father

55:05.511 --> 55:07.553
and you don't get to write
about my mother.

55:07.638 --> 55:09.806
In fact, stop writing me at all.

55:09.890 --> 55:11.182
Stop writing me letters.

55:11.266 --> 55:12.350
You should save them.

55:12.434 --> 55:14.143
They'll be worth money someday.

55:14.228 --> 55:16.354
I have saved them, actually.

55:16.438 --> 55:18.147
I have over 100. That's enough.

55:18.232 --> 55:19.691
You saved them. Good.

55:21.318 --> 55:25.071
You bring liquor in here again,
you are barred. End of story.

55:25.155 --> 55:27.699
Eano the Beano tells me
you are into drugs.

55:27.783 --> 55:30.785
Who the fuck is Eano the Beano?
How would he know that?

55:30.869 --> 55:32.912
Everybody knows, the word is out.

55:33.080 --> 55:35.164
You know, if so, good luck to you.

55:35.249 --> 55:36.874
But don't waste your talent.

55:36.959 --> 55:38.292
I don't have any talent.

55:38.377 --> 55:39.961
I find that hard to believe.

55:40.045 --> 55:42.380
Why? Because you're so
incredibly talented?

55:42.464 --> 55:43.464
Yes.

55:43.549 --> 55:45.174
Okay, so where is it?

55:45.801 --> 55:47.427
The masterpiece.

55:48.971 --> 55:51.014
Where are you hiding it?

55:51.098 --> 55:52.640
Can I read it? Does it even exist?

55:52.725 --> 55:54.392
Do you exist, Nicholas Flynn?

55:54.768 --> 55:55.852
Do you even know?

55:55.936 --> 55:58.813
I, Jonathan Flynn, exist!
I know that much.

55:58.897 --> 56:00.523
Jonathan Flynn exists!

56:00.607 --> 56:01.691
MAN: Shut the fuck up!

56:01.775 --> 56:03.359
You shut the fuck up,

56:03.444 --> 56:05.445
or my son will evict you!

56:06.947 --> 56:08.156
I want you to leave here.

56:08.240 --> 56:10.533
Find some fucking place,

56:10.617 --> 56:13.536
some old drinking buddy who is suicidal
enough to take you in.

56:13.620 --> 56:15.538
I'm a sought-after house guest.

56:15.622 --> 56:17.874
Yeah, because you're an excellent
raconteur. Right?

56:17.958 --> 56:19.000
Yes! Good night!

56:19.084 --> 56:20.585
Remember something, Nicholas.

56:20.669 --> 56:22.378
You are me!

56:22.463 --> 56:23.963
You are me! I made you!

56:24.048 --> 56:25.048
(MEN CLAMORING)

56:25.132 --> 56:26.549
You are me!

56:26.633 --> 56:29.218
I am not you! I am not you!

56:29.303 --> 56:31.137
Yes, you are! Go to Florida!

56:31.221 --> 56:33.056
You are me!

56:33.140 --> 56:34.640
(MEN CLAMORING)

56:34.725 --> 56:38.227
MAN: Shut the fuck up! Everybody,
shut the fuck up!

56:38.312 --> 56:39.520
Night.

56:41.440 --> 56:43.566
NICK: I asked to fill in
on the outreach van.

56:43.650 --> 56:45.193
I can't stand to be in the shelter

56:45.277 --> 56:48.362
where my drunken jack-in-the-box
can appear at any moment.

56:48.447 --> 56:51.449
Hey, you are the guy whose father
is a guest here, aren't you?

56:51.533 --> 56:53.576
No. That guy is just a drunk.

56:53.994 --> 56:56.746
A con man, he has nothing to do with me.

56:56.830 --> 56:58.831
Yeah. No, of course not.

56:59.124 --> 57:00.374
Okay, we're ready.

57:00.459 --> 57:01.542
Yeah. Okay.

57:01.627 --> 57:04.003
The hours are 9:00 at night
until 5:00 in the morning.

57:05.214 --> 57:06.506
Hi, I got a sandwich for you.

57:09.009 --> 57:12.929
Hey, excuse me, sir, sorry to wake you.

57:13.013 --> 57:15.056
I got a sandwich here.

57:16.558 --> 57:17.600
You want to get inside?

57:25.651 --> 57:26.859
(BOTTLE SHATTERS)

57:27.319 --> 57:30.780
"Jonathan Flynn responded to a guest's request
that he share a can of deodorant

57:30.864 --> 57:32.782
"with an intense verbal assault towards

57:32.866 --> 57:35.910
"the other guest on racial
and sexual themes.

57:35.994 --> 57:38.204
"Mr. Flynn would not respond
to intervention.

57:38.288 --> 57:40.957
"In fact, he accelerated
his verbal assault."

57:41.041 --> 57:42.542
Are you okay?

57:43.210 --> 57:44.335
Yeah.

57:45.462 --> 57:48.214
Jonathan's a little out
of control tonight.

57:50.717 --> 57:53.803
"The SPO, Chris, Gabriel, and Brian,

57:53.887 --> 57:57.306
"escorted Mr. Flynn to the brown
lobby wrapped in a sheet,

57:57.391 --> 57:59.892
"as he had refused to dress himself."

57:59.977 --> 58:02.979
...my vision, The Confessions
of Christopher Cobb.

58:03.063 --> 58:04.689
My father rants... "In the
beginning was the Word."

58:04.773 --> 58:05.815
Salinger, Twain...

58:05.899 --> 58:09.152
...piss on the floor unnoticed.
...Jonathan Robinson Flynn.

58:09.236 --> 58:11.571
I was brought into this world
to help other people.

58:11.655 --> 58:12.655
Ignored.

58:12.739 --> 58:16.117
I was brought into this world to write
my masterpiece, and it's written!

58:16.577 --> 58:17.994
We all need to create the story

58:18.078 --> 58:19.662
that will make sense of our lives.

58:19.746 --> 58:21.164
I stood behind the priest
and held his robe...

58:21.248 --> 58:22.540
Make sense of our daily tasks.

58:22.624 --> 58:24.083
